43/* Parse the -femit-struct-debug-detailed option value
44 and set the flag variables. */
45
46#define MATCH( prefix, string ) \
47 ((strncmp (prefix, string, sizeof prefix - 1) == 0) \
48 ? ((string += sizeof prefix - 1), 1) : 0)
49
50void
51set_struct_debug_option (struct gcc_options *opts, location_t loc,
52 const char *spec)
53{
54 /* various labels for comparison */
55 static const char dfn_lbl[] = "dfn:", dir_lbl[] = "dir:", ind_lbl[] = "ind:";
56 static const char ord_lbl[] = "ord:", gen_lbl[] = "gen:";
57 static const char none_lbl[] = "none", any_lbl[] = "any";
58 static const char base_lbl[] = "base", sys_lbl[] = "sys";
59
60 enum debug_struct_file files = DINFO_STRUCT_FILE_ANY;
61 /* Default is to apply to as much as possible. */
62 enum debug_info_usage usage = DINFO_USAGE_NUM_ENUMS;
63 int ord = 1, gen = 1;
64
65 /* What usage? */
66 if (MATCH (dfn_lbl, spec))
67 usage = DINFO_USAGE_DFN;
68 else if (MATCH (dir_lbl, spec))
69 usage = DINFO_USAGE_DIR_USE;
70 else if (MATCH (ind_lbl, spec))
71 usage = DINFO_USAGE_IND_USE;
72
73 /* Generics or not? */
74 if (MATCH (ord_lbl, spec))
75 gen = 0;
76 else if (MATCH (gen_lbl, spec))
77 ord = 0;
78
79 /* What allowable environment? */
80 if (MATCH (none_lbl, spec))
81 files = DINFO_STRUCT_FILE_NONE;
82 else if (MATCH (any_lbl, spec))
83 files = DINFO_STRUCT_FILE_ANY;
84 else if (MATCH (sys_lbl, spec))
85 files = DINFO_STRUCT_FILE_SYS;
86 else if (MATCH (base_lbl, spec))
87 files = DINFO_STRUCT_FILE_BASE;
88 else
89 error_at (loc,
90 "argument %qs to %<-femit-struct-debug-detailed%> "
91 "not recognized",
92 spec);
93
94 /* Effect the specification. */
95 if (usage == DINFO_USAGE_NUM_ENUMS)
96 {
97 if (ord)
98 {
99 opts->x_debug_struct_ordinary[DINFO_USAGE_DFN] = files;
100 opts->x_debug_struct_ordinary[DINFO_USAGE_DIR_USE] = files;
101 opts->x_debug_struct_ordinary[DINFO_USAGE_IND_USE] = files;
102 }
103 if (gen)
104 {
105 opts->x_debug_struct_generic[DINFO_USAGE_DFN] = files;
106 opts->x_debug_struct_generic[DINFO_USAGE_DIR_USE] = files;
107 opts->x_debug_struct_generic[DINFO_USAGE_IND_USE] = files;
108 }
109 }
110 else
111 {
112 if (ord)
113 opts->x_debug_struct_ordinary[usage] = files;
114 if (gen)
115 opts->x_debug_struct_generic[usage] = files;
116 }
117
118 if (*spec == ',')
119 set_struct_debug_option (opts, loc, spec+1);
120 else
121 {
122 /* No more -femit-struct-debug-detailed specifications.
123 Do final checks. */
124 if (*spec != '\0')
125 error_at (loc,
126 "argument %qs to %<-femit-struct-debug-detailed%> unknown",
127 spec);
128 if (opts->x_debug_struct_ordinary[DINFO_USAGE_DIR_USE]
129 < opts->x_debug_struct_ordinary[DINFO_USAGE_IND_USE]
130 || opts->x_debug_struct_generic[DINFO_USAGE_DIR_USE]
131 < opts->x_debug_struct_generic[DINFO_USAGE_IND_USE])
132 error_at (loc,
133 "%<-femit-struct-debug-detailed=dir:...%> must allow "
134 "at least as much as "
135 "%<-femit-struct-debug-detailed=ind:...%>");
136 }
137}

139/* Strip off a legitimate source ending from the input string NAME of
140 length LEN. Rather than having to know the names used by all of
141 our front ends, we strip off an ending of a period followed by
142 up to five characters. (Java uses ".class".) */
143
144void
145strip_off_ending (char *name, int len)
146{
147 int i;
148 for (i = 2; i < 6 && len > i; i++)
149 {
150 if (name[len - i] == '.')
151 {
152 name[len - i] = '\0';
153 break;
154 }
155 }
156}

158/* Find the base name of a path, stripping off both directories and
159 a single final extension. */
160int
161base_of_path (const char *path, const char **base_out)
162{
163 const char *base = path;
164 const char *dot = 0;
165 const char *p = path;
166 char c = *p;
167 while (c)
168 {
169 if (IS_DIR_SEPARATOR (c))
170 {
171 base = p + 1;
172 dot = 0;
173 }
174 else if (c == '.')
175 dot = p;
176 c = *++p;
177 }
178 if (!dot)
179 dot = p;
180 *base_out = base;
181 return dot - base;
182}

227/* Add comma-separated strings to a char_p vector. */
228
229static void
230add_comma_separated_to_vector (void **pvec, const char *arg)
231{
232 char *tmp;
233 char *r;
234 char *w;
235 char *token_start;
236 vec<char_p> *v = (vec<char_p> *) *pvec;
237
238 vec_check_alloc (v, 1);
239
240 /* We never free this string. */
241 tmp = xstrdup (arg);
242
243 r = tmp;
244 w = tmp;
245 token_start = tmp;
246
247 while (*r != '\0')
248 {
249 if (*r == ',')
250 {
251 *w++ = '\0';
252 ++r;
253 v->safe_push (token_start);
254 token_start = w;
255 }
256 if (*r == '\\' && r[1] == ',')
257 {
258 *w++ = ',';
259 r += 2;
260 }
261 else
262 *w++ = *r++;
263 }
264 if (*token_start != '\0')
265 v->safe_push (token_start);
266
267 *pvec = v;
268}

278/* Initialize OPTS and OPTS_SET before using them in parsing options. */
279
280void
281init_options_struct (struct gcc_options *opts, struct gcc_options *opts_set)
282{
283 size_t num_params = get_num_compiler_params ();
284
285 /* Ensure that opts_obstack has already been initialized by the time
286 that we initialize any gcc_options instances (PR jit/68446). */
287 gcc_assert (opts_obstack.chunk_size > 0);
288
289 *opts = global_options_init;
290
291 if (opts_set)
292 memset (opts_set, 0, sizeof (*opts_set));
293
294 opts->x_param_values = XNEWVEC (int, num_params);
295
296 if (opts_set)
297 opts_set->x_param_values = XCNEWVEC (int, num_params);
298
299 init_param_values (opts->x_param_values);
300
301 /* Initialize whether `char' is signed. */
302 opts->x_flag_signed_char = DEFAULT_SIGNED_CHAR;
303 /* Set this to a special "uninitialized" value. The actual default
304 is set after target options have been processed. */
305 opts->x_flag_short_enums = 2;
306
307 /* Initialize target_flags before default_options_optimization
308 so the latter can modify it. */
309 opts->x_target_flags = targetm_common.default_target_flags;
310
311 /* Some targets have ABI-specified unwind tables. */
312 opts->x_flag_unwind_tables = targetm_common.unwind_tables_default;
313
314 /* Some targets have other target-specific initialization. */
315 targetm_common.option_init_struct (opts);
316}

318/* Release any allocations owned by OPTS. */
319
320void
321finalize_options_struct (struct gcc_options *opts)
322{
323 XDELETEVEC (opts->x_param_values);
324}

326/* If indicated by the optimization level LEVEL (-Os if SIZE is set,
327 -Ofast if FAST is set, -Og if DEBUG is set), apply the option DEFAULT_OPT
328 to OPTS and OPTS_SET, diagnostic context DC, location LOC, with language
329 mask LANG_MASK and option handlers HANDLERS. */
330
331static void
332maybe_default_option (struct gcc_options *opts,
333 struct gcc_options *opts_set,
334 const struct default_options *default_opt,
335 int level, bool size, bool fast, bool debug,
336 unsigned int lang_mask,
337 const struct cl_option_handlers *handlers,
338 location_t loc,
339 diagnostic_context *dc)
340{
341 const struct cl_option *option = &cl_options[default_opt->opt_index];
342 bool enabled;
343
344 if (size)
345 gcc_assert (level == 2);
346 if (fast)
347 gcc_assert (level == 3);
348 if (debug)
349 gcc_assert (level == 1);
350
351 switch (default_opt->levels)
352 {
353 case OPT_LEVELS_ALL:
354 enabled = true;
355 break;
356
357 case OPT_LEVELS_0_ONLY:
358 enabled = (level == 0);
359 break;
360
361 case OPT_LEVELS_1_PLUS:
362 enabled = (level >= 1);
363 break;
364
365 case OPT_LEVELS_1_PLUS_SPEED_ONLY:
366 enabled = (level >= 1 && !size && !debug);
367 break;
368
369 case OPT_LEVELS_1_PLUS_NOT_DEBUG:
370 enabled = (level >= 1 && !debug);
371 break;
372
373 case OPT_LEVELS_2_PLUS:
374 enabled = (level >= 2);
375 break;
376
377 case OPT_LEVELS_2_PLUS_SPEED_ONLY:
378 enabled = (level >= 2 && !size && !debug);
379 break;
380
381 case OPT_LEVELS_3_PLUS:
382 enabled = (level >= 3);
383 break;
384
385 case OPT_LEVELS_3_PLUS_AND_SIZE:
386 enabled = (level >= 3 || size);
387 break;
388
389 case OPT_LEVELS_SIZE:
390 enabled = size;
391 break;
392
393 case OPT_LEVELS_FAST:
394 enabled = fast;
395 break;
396
397 case OPT_LEVELS_NONE:
398 default:
399 gcc_unreachable ();
400 }
401
402 if (enabled)
403 handle_generated_option (opts, opts_set, default_opt->opt_index,
404 default_opt->arg, default_opt->value,
405 lang_mask, DK_UNSPECIFIED, loc,
406 handlers, true, dc);
407 else if (default_opt->arg == NULL
408 && !option->cl_reject_negative)
409 handle_generated_option (opts, opts_set, default_opt->opt_index,
410 default_opt->arg, !default_opt->value,
411 lang_mask, DK_UNSPECIFIED, loc,
412 handlers, true, dc);
413}
414
415/* As indicated by the optimization level LEVEL (-Os if SIZE is set,
416 -Ofast if FAST is set), apply the options in array DEFAULT_OPTS to
417 OPTS and OPTS_SET, diagnostic context DC, location LOC, with
418 language mask LANG_MASK and option handlers HANDLERS. */
419
420static void
421maybe_default_options (struct gcc_options *opts,
422 struct gcc_options *opts_set,
423 const struct default_options *default_opts,
424 int level, bool size, bool fast, bool debug,
425 unsigned int lang_mask,
426 const struct cl_option_handlers *handlers,
427 location_t loc,
428 diagnostic_context *dc)
429{
430 size_t i;
431
432 for (i = 0; default_opts[i].levels != OPT_LEVELS_NONE; i++)
433 maybe_default_option (opts, opts_set, &default_opts[i],
434 level, size, fast, debug,
435 lang_mask, handlers, loc, dc);
436}

551/* Default the options in OPTS and OPTS_SET based on the optimization
552 settings in DECODED_OPTIONS and DECODED_OPTIONS_COUNT. */
553void
554default_options_optimization (struct gcc_options *opts,
555 struct gcc_options *opts_set,
556 struct cl_decoded_option *decoded_options,
557 unsigned int decoded_options_count,
558 location_t loc,
559 unsigned int lang_mask,
560 const struct cl_option_handlers *handlers,
561 diagnostic_context *dc)
562{
563 unsigned int i;
564 int opt2;
565 bool openacc_mode = false;
566
567 /* Scan to see what optimization level has been specified. That will
568 determine the default value of many flags. */
569 for (i = 1; i < decoded_options_count; i++)
570 {
571 struct cl_decoded_option *opt = &decoded_options[i];
572 switch (opt->opt_index)
573 {
574 case OPT_O:
575 if (*opt->arg == '\0')
576 {
577 opts->x_optimize = 1;
578 opts->x_optimize_size = 0;
579 opts->x_optimize_fast = 0;
580 opts->x_optimize_debug = 0;
581 }
582 else
583 {
584 const int optimize_val = integral_argument (opt->arg);
585 if (optimize_val == -1)
586 error_at (loc, "argument to %<-O%> should be a non-negative "
587 "integer, %<g%>, %<s%> or %<fast%>");
588 else
589 {
590 opts->x_optimize = optimize_val;
591 if ((unsigned int) opts->x_optimize > 255)
592 opts->x_optimize = 255;
593 opts->x_optimize_size = 0;
594 opts->x_optimize_fast = 0;
595 opts->x_optimize_debug = 0;
596 }
597 }
598 break;
599
600 case OPT_Os:
601 opts->x_optimize_size = 1;
602
603 /* Optimizing for size forces optimize to be 2. */
604 opts->x_optimize = 2;
605 opts->x_optimize_fast = 0;
606 opts->x_optimize_debug = 0;
607 break;
608
609 case OPT_Ofast:
610 /* -Ofast only adds flags to -O3. */
611 opts->x_optimize_size = 0;
612 opts->x_optimize = 3;
613 opts->x_optimize_fast = 1;
614 opts->x_optimize_debug = 0;
615 break;
616
617 case OPT_Og:
618 /* -Og selects optimization level 1. */
619 opts->x_optimize_size = 0;
620 opts->x_optimize = 1;
621 opts->x_optimize_fast = 0;
622 opts->x_optimize_debug = 1;
623 break;
624
625 case OPT_fopenacc:
626 if (opt->value)
627 openacc_mode = true;
628 break;
629
630 default:
631 /* Ignore other options in this prescan. */
632 break;
633 }
634 }
635
636 maybe_default_options (opts, opts_set, default_options_table,
637 opts->x_optimize, opts->x_optimize_size,
638 opts->x_optimize_fast, opts->x_optimize_debug,
639 lang_mask, handlers, loc, dc);
640
641 /* -O2 param settings. */
642 opt2 = (opts->x_optimize >= 2);
643
644 if (openacc_mode
645 && !opts_set->x_flag_ipa_pta)
646 opts->x_flag_ipa_pta = true;
647
648 /* Track fields in field-sensitive alias analysis. */
649 maybe_set_param_value
650 (PARAM_MAX_FIELDS_FOR_FIELD_SENSITIVE,
651 opt2 ? 100 : default_param_value (PARAM_MAX_FIELDS_FOR_FIELD_SENSITIVE),
652 opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
653
654 /* For -O1 only do loop invariant motion for very small loops. */
655 maybe_set_param_value
656 (PARAM_LOOP_INVARIANT_MAX_BBS_IN_LOOP,
657 opt2 ? default_param_value (PARAM_LOOP_INVARIANT_MAX_BBS_IN_LOOP) : 1000,
658 opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
659
660 /* At -Ofast, allow store motion to introduce potential race conditions. */
661 maybe_set_param_value
662 (PARAM_ALLOW_STORE_DATA_RACES,
663 opts->x_optimize_fast ? 1
664 : default_param_value (PARAM_ALLOW_STORE_DATA_RACES),
665 opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
666
667 if (opts->x_optimize_size)
668 /* We want to crossjump as much as possible. */
669 maybe_set_param_value (PARAM_MIN_CROSSJUMP_INSNS, 1,
670 opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
671 else
672 maybe_set_param_value (PARAM_MIN_CROSSJUMP_INSNS,
673 default_param_value (PARAM_MIN_CROSSJUMP_INSNS),
674 opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
675
676 /* Restrict the amount of work combine does at -Og while retaining
677 most of its useful transforms. */
678 if (opts->x_optimize_debug)
679 maybe_set_param_value (PARAM_MAX_COMBINE_INSNS, 2,
680 opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
681
682 /* Allow default optimizations to be specified on a per-machine basis. */
683 maybe_default_options (opts, opts_set,
684 targetm_common.option_optimization_table,
685 opts->x_optimize, opts->x_optimize_size,
686 opts->x_optimize_fast, opts->x_optimize_debug,
687 lang_mask, handlers, loc, dc);
688}
689
690/* After all options at LOC have been read into OPTS and OPTS_SET,
691 finalize settings of those options and diagnose incompatible
692 combinations. */
693void
694finish_options (struct gcc_options *opts, struct gcc_options *opts_set,
695 location_t loc)
696{
697 enum unwind_info_type ui_except;
698
699 if (opts->x_dump_base_name
700 && ! IS_ABSOLUTE_PATH (opts->x_dump_base_name)
701 && ! opts->x_dump_base_name_prefixed)
702 {
703 /* First try to make OPTS->X_DUMP_BASE_NAME relative to the
704 OPTS->X_DUMP_DIR_NAME directory. Then try to make
705 OPTS->X_DUMP_BASE_NAME relative to the OPTS->X_AUX_BASE_NAME
706 directory, typically the directory to contain the object
707 file. */
708 if (opts->x_dump_dir_name)
709 opts->x_dump_base_name = opts_concat (opts->x_dump_dir_name,
710 opts->x_dump_base_name, NULL);
711 else if (opts->x_aux_base_name
712 && strcmp (opts->x_aux_base_name, HOST_BIT_BUCKET) != 0)
713 {
714 const char *aux_base;
715
716 base_of_path (opts->x_aux_base_name, &aux_base);
717 if (opts->x_aux_base_name != aux_base)
718 {
719 int dir_len = aux_base - opts->x_aux_base_name;
720 char *new_dump_base_name
721 = XOBNEWVEC (&opts_obstack, char,
722 strlen (opts->x_dump_base_name) + dir_len + 1);
723
724 /* Copy directory component from OPTS->X_AUX_BASE_NAME. */
725 memcpy (new_dump_base_name, opts->x_aux_base_name, dir_len);
726 /* Append existing OPTS->X_DUMP_BASE_NAME. */
727 strcpy (new_dump_base_name + dir_len, opts->x_dump_base_name);
728 opts->x_dump_base_name = new_dump_base_name;
729 }
730 }
731 opts->x_dump_base_name_prefixed = true;
732 }
733
734 /* Handle related options for unit-at-a-time, toplevel-reorder, and
735 section-anchors. */
736 if (!opts->x_flag_unit_at_a_time)
737 {
738 if (opts->x_flag_section_anchors && opts_set->x_flag_section_anchors)
739 error_at (loc, "section anchors must be disabled when unit-at-a-time "
740 "is disabled");
741 opts->x_flag_section_anchors = 0;
742 if (opts->x_flag_toplevel_reorder == 1)
743 error_at (loc, "toplevel reorder must be disabled when unit-at-a-time "
744 "is disabled");
745 opts->x_flag_toplevel_reorder = 0;
746 }
747
748 /* -fself-test depends on the state of the compiler prior to
749 compiling anything. Ideally it should be run on an empty source
750 file. However, in case we get run with actual source, assume
751 -fsyntax-only which will inhibit any compiler initialization
752 which may confuse the self tests. */
753 if (opts->x_flag_self_test)
754 opts->x_flag_syntax_only = 1;
755
756 if (opts->x_flag_tm && opts->x_flag_non_call_exceptions)
757 sorry ("transactional memory is not supported with non-call exceptions");
758
759 /* Unless the user has asked for section anchors, we disable toplevel
760 reordering at -O0 to disable transformations that might be surprising
761 to end users and to get -fno-toplevel-reorder tested. */
762 if (!opts->x_optimize
763 && opts->x_flag_toplevel_reorder == 2
764 && !(opts->x_flag_section_anchors && opts_set->x_flag_section_anchors))
765 {
766 opts->x_flag_toplevel_reorder = 0;
767 opts->x_flag_section_anchors = 0;
768 }
769 if (!opts->x_flag_toplevel_reorder)
770 {
771 if (opts->x_flag_section_anchors && opts_set->x_flag_section_anchors)
772 error_at (loc, "section anchors must be disabled when toplevel reorder"
773 " is disabled");
774 opts->x_flag_section_anchors = 0;
775 }
776
777 if (!opts->x_flag_opts_finished)
778 {
779 /* We initialize opts->x_flag_pie to -1 so that targets can set a
780 default value. */
781 if (opts->x_flag_pie == -1)
782 {
783 /* We initialize opts->x_flag_pic to -1 so that we can tell if
784 -fpic, -fPIC, -fno-pic or -fno-PIC is used. */
785 if (opts->x_flag_pic == -1)
786 opts->x_flag_pie = DEFAULT_FLAG_PIE;
787 else
788 opts->x_flag_pie = 0;
789 }
790 /* If -fPIE or -fpie is used, turn on PIC. */
791 if (opts->x_flag_pie)
792 opts->x_flag_pic = opts->x_flag_pie;
793 else if (opts->x_flag_pic == -1)
794 opts->x_flag_pic = 0;
795 if (opts->x_flag_pic && !opts->x_flag_pie)
796 opts->x_flag_shlib = 1;
797 opts->x_flag_opts_finished = true;
798 }
799
800 /* We initialize opts->x_flag_stack_protect to -1 so that targets
801 can set a default value. */
802 if (opts->x_flag_stack_protect == -1)
803 opts->x_flag_stack_protect = DEFAULT_FLAG_SSP;
804
805 if (opts->x_optimize == 0)
806 {
807 /* Inlining does not work if not optimizing,
808 so force it not to be done. */
809 opts->x_warn_inline = 0;
810 opts->x_flag_no_inline = 1;
811 }
812
813 /* The optimization to partition hot and cold basic blocks into separate
814 sections of the .o and executable files does not work (currently)
815 with exception handling. This is because there is no support for
816 generating unwind info. If opts->x_flag_exceptions is turned on
817 we need to turn off the partitioning optimization. */
818
819 ui_except = targetm_common.except_unwind_info (opts);
820
821 if (opts->x_flag_exceptions
822 && opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition
823 && (ui_except == UI_SJLJ || ui_except >= UI_TARGET))
824 {
825 if (opts_set->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition)
826 inform (loc,
827 "-freorder-blocks-and-partition does not work "
828 "with exceptions on this architecture");
829 opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition = 0;
830 opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks = 1;
831 }
832
833 /* If user requested unwind info, then turn off the partitioning
834 optimization. */
835
836 if (opts->x_flag_unwind_tables
837 && !targetm_common.unwind_tables_default
838 && opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition
839 && (ui_except == UI_SJLJ || ui_except >= UI_TARGET))
840 {
841 if (opts_set->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition)
842 inform (loc,
843 "-freorder-blocks-and-partition does not support "
844 "unwind info on this architecture");
845 opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition = 0;
846 opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks = 1;
847 }
848
849 /* If the target requested unwind info, then turn off the partitioning
850 optimization with a different message. Likewise, if the target does not
851 support named sections. */
852
853 if (opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition
854 && (!targetm_common.have_named_sections
855 || (opts->x_flag_unwind_tables
856 && targetm_common.unwind_tables_default
857 && (ui_except == UI_SJLJ || ui_except >= UI_TARGET))))
858 {
859 if (opts_set->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition)
860 inform (loc,
861 "-freorder-blocks-and-partition does not work "
862 "on this architecture");
863 opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition = 0;
864 opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks = 1;
865 }
866
867 /* Disable -freorder-blocks-and-partition when -fprofile-use is not in
868 effect. Function splitting was not actually being performed in that case,
869 as probably_never_executed_bb_p does not distinguish any basic blocks as
870 being cold vs hot when there is no profile data. Leaving it enabled,
871 however, causes the assembly code generator to create (empty) cold
872 sections and labels, leading to unnecessary size overhead. */
873 if (opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition
874 && !opts_set->x_flag_profile_use)
875 opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition = 0;
876
877 if (opts->x_flag_reorder_blocks_and_partition
878 && !opts_set->x_flag_reorder_functions)
879 opts->x_flag_reorder_functions = 1;
880
881 /* Pipelining of outer loops is only possible when general pipelining
882 capabilities are requested. */
883 if (!opts->x_flag_sel_sched_pipelining)
884 opts->x_flag_sel_sched_pipelining_outer_loops = 0;
885
886 if (opts->x_flag_conserve_stack)
887 {
888 maybe_set_param_value (PARAM_LARGE_STACK_FRAME, 100,
889 opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
890 maybe_set_param_value (PARAM_STACK_FRAME_GROWTH, 40,
891 opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
892 }
893
894 if (opts->x_flag_lto)
895 {
896#ifdef ENABLE_LTO
897 opts->x_flag_generate_lto = 1;
898
899 /* When generating IL, do not operate in whole-program mode.
900 Otherwise, symbols will be privatized too early, causing link
901 errors later. */
902 opts->x_flag_whole_program = 0;
903#else
904 error_at (loc, "LTO support has not been enabled in this configuration");
905#endif
906 if (!opts->x_flag_fat_lto_objects
907 && (!HAVE_LTO_PLUGIN
908 || (opts_set->x_flag_use_linker_plugin
909 && !opts->x_flag_use_linker_plugin)))
910 {
911 if (opts_set->x_flag_fat_lto_objects)
912 error_at (loc, "-fno-fat-lto-objects are supported only with linker plugin");
913 opts->x_flag_fat_lto_objects = 1;
914 }
915 }
916
917 /* We initialize opts->x_flag_split_stack to -1 so that targets can set a
918 default value if they choose based on other options. */
919 if (opts->x_flag_split_stack == -1)
920 opts->x_flag_split_stack = 0;
921 else if (opts->x_flag_split_stack)
922 {
923 if (!targetm_common.supports_split_stack (true, opts))
924 {
925 error_at (loc, "%<-fsplit-stack%> is not supported by "
926 "this compiler configuration");
927 opts->x_flag_split_stack = 0;
928 }
929 }
930
931 /* Tune vectorization related parametees according to cost model. */
932 if (opts->x_flag_vect_cost_model == VECT_COST_MODEL_CHEAP)
933 {
934 maybe_set_param_value (PARAM_VECT_MAX_VERSION_FOR_ALIAS_CHECKS,
935 6, opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
936 maybe_set_param_value (PARAM_VECT_MAX_VERSION_FOR_ALIGNMENT_CHECKS,
937 0, opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
938 maybe_set_param_value (PARAM_VECT_MAX_PEELING_FOR_ALIGNMENT,
939 0, opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
940 }
941
942 /* Set PARAM_MAX_STORES_TO_SINK to 0 if either vectorization or if-conversion
943 is disabled. */
944 if ((!opts->x_flag_tree_loop_vectorize && !opts->x_flag_tree_slp_vectorize)
945 || !opts->x_flag_tree_loop_if_convert)
946 maybe_set_param_value (PARAM_MAX_STORES_TO_SINK, 0,
947 opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
948
949 /* The -gsplit-dwarf option requires -ggnu-pubnames. */
950 if (opts->x_dwarf_split_debug_info)
951 opts->x_debug_generate_pub_sections = 2;
952
953 /* Userspace and kernel ASan conflict with each other. */
954 if ((opts->x_flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_USER_ADDRESS)
955 && (opts->x_flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_KERNEL_ADDRESS))
956 error_at (loc,
957 "-fsanitize=address is incompatible with "
958 "-fsanitize=kernel-address");
959
960 /* And with TSan. */
961 if ((opts->x_flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_ADDRESS)
962 && (opts->x_flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_THREAD))
963 error_at (loc,
964 "-fsanitize=address and -fsanitize=kernel-address "
965 "are incompatible with -fsanitize=thread");
966
967 if ((opts->x_flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_LEAK)
968 && (opts->x_flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_THREAD))
969 error_at (loc,
970 "-fsanitize=leak is incompatible with -fsanitize=thread");
971
972 /* Check error recovery for -fsanitize-recover option. */
973 for (int i = 0; sanitizer_opts[i].name != NULL; ++i)
974 if ((opts->x_flag_sanitize_recover & sanitizer_opts[i].flag)
975 && !sanitizer_opts[i].can_recover)
976 error_at (loc, "-fsanitize-recover=%s is not supported",
977 sanitizer_opts[i].name);
978
979 /* When instrumenting the pointers, we don't want to remove
980 the null pointer checks. */
981 if (opts->x_flag_sanitize & (SANITIZE_NULL | SANITIZE_NONNULL_ATTRIBUTE
982 | SANITIZE_RETURNS_NONNULL_ATTRIBUTE))
983 opts->x_flag_delete_null_pointer_checks = 0;
984
985 /* Aggressive compiler optimizations may cause false negatives. */
986 if (opts->x_flag_sanitize & ~(SANITIZE_LEAK | SANITIZE_UNREACHABLE))
987 {
988 opts->x_flag_aggressive_loop_optimizations = 0;
989 opts->x_flag_strict_overflow = 0;
990 }
991
992 /* Enable -fsanitize-address-use-after-scope if address sanitizer is
993 enabled. */
994 if ((opts->x_flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_USER_ADDRESS)
995 && !opts_set->x_flag_sanitize_address_use_after_scope)
996 opts->x_flag_sanitize_address_use_after_scope = true;
997
998 /* Force -fstack-reuse=none in case -fsanitize-address-use-after-scope
999 is enabled. */
1000 if (opts->x_flag_sanitize_address_use_after_scope)
1001 {
1002 if (opts->x_flag_stack_reuse != SR_NONE
1003 && opts_set->x_flag_stack_reuse != SR_NONE)
1004 error_at (loc,
1005 "-fsanitize-address-use-after-scope requires "
1006 "-fstack-reuse=none option");
1007
1008 opts->x_flag_stack_reuse = SR_NONE;
1009 }
1010
1011 if ((opts->x_flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_USER_ADDRESS) && opts->x_flag_tm)
1012 sorry ("transactional memory is not supported with %<-fsanitize=address%>");
1013
1014 if ((opts->x_flag_sanitize & SANITIZE_KERNEL_ADDRESS) && opts->x_flag_tm)
1015 sorry ("transactional memory is not supported with "
1016 "%<-fsanitize=kernel-address%>");
1017
1018 /* Comes from final.c -- no real reason to change it. */
1019#define MAX_CODE_ALIGN 16
1020#define MAX_CODE_ALIGN_VALUE (1 << MAX_CODE_ALIGN)
1021
1022 if (opts->x_align_loops > MAX_CODE_ALIGN_VALUE)
1023 error_at (loc, "-falign-loops=%d is not between 0 and %d",
1024 opts->x_align_loops, MAX_CODE_ALIGN_VALUE);
1025
1026 if (opts->x_align_jumps > MAX_CODE_ALIGN_VALUE)
1027 error_at (loc, "-falign-jumps=%d is not between 0 and %d",
1028 opts->x_align_jumps, MAX_CODE_ALIGN_VALUE);
1029
1030 if (opts->x_align_functions > MAX_CODE_ALIGN_VALUE)
1031 error_at (loc, "-falign-functions=%d is not between 0 and %d",
1032 opts->x_align_functions, MAX_CODE_ALIGN_VALUE);
1033
1034 if (opts->x_align_labels > MAX_CODE_ALIGN_VALUE)
1035 error_at (loc, "-falign-labels=%d is not between 0 and %d",
1036 opts->x_align_labels, MAX_CODE_ALIGN_VALUE);
1037}
1038
1039#define LEFT_COLUMN 27
1040
1041/* Output ITEM, of length ITEM_WIDTH, in the left column,
1042 followed by word-wrapped HELP in a second column. */
1043static void
1044wrap_help (const char *help,
1045 const char *item,
1046 unsigned int item_width,
1047 unsigned int columns)
1048{
1049 unsigned int col_width = LEFT_COLUMN;
1050 unsigned int remaining, room, len;
1051
1052 remaining = strlen (help);
1053
1054 do
1055 {
1056 room = columns - 3 - MAX (col_width, item_width);
1057 if (room > columns)
1058 room = 0;
1059 len = remaining;
1060
1061 if (room < len)
1062 {
1063 unsigned int i;
1064
1065 for (i = 0; help[i]; i++)
1066 {
1067 if (i >= room && len != remaining)
1068 break;
1069 if (help[i] == ' ')
1070 len = i;
1071 else if ((help[i] == '-' || help[i] == '/')
1072 && help[i + 1] != ' '
1073 && i > 0 && ISALPHA (help[i - 1]))
1074 len = i + 1;
1075 }
1076 }
1077
1078 printf (" %-*.*s %.*s\n", col_width, item_width, item, len, help);
1079 item_width = 0;
1080 while (help[len] == ' ')
1081 len++;
1082 help += len;
1083 remaining -= len;
1084 }
1085 while (remaining);
1086}
1087
1088/* Print help for a specific front-end, etc. */
1089static void
1090print_filtered_help (unsigned int include_flags,
1091 unsigned int exclude_flags,
1092 unsigned int any_flags,
1093 unsigned int columns,
1094 struct gcc_options *opts,
1095 unsigned int lang_mask)
1096{
1097 unsigned int i;
1098 const char *help;
1099 bool found = false;
1100 bool displayed = false;
1101 char new_help[256];
1102
1103 if (include_flags == CL_PARAMS)
1104 {
1105 for (i = 0; i < LAST_PARAM; i++)
1106 {
1107 const char *param = compiler_params[i].option;
1108
1109 help = compiler_params[i].help;
1110 if (help == NULL || *help == '\0')
1111 {
1112 if (exclude_flags & CL_UNDOCUMENTED)
1113 continue;
1114 help = undocumented_msg;
1115 }
1116
1117 /* Get the translation. */
1118 help = _(help);
1119
1120 if (!opts->x_quiet_flag)
1121 {
1122 snprintf (new_help, sizeof (new_help),
1123 _("default %d minimum %d maximum %d"),
1124 compiler_params[i].default_value,
1125 compiler_params[i].min_value,
1126 compiler_params[i].max_value);
1127 help = new_help;
1128 }
1129 wrap_help (help, param, strlen (param), columns);
1130 }
1131 putchar ('\n');
1132 return;
1133 }
1134
1135 if (!opts->x_help_printed)
1136 opts->x_help_printed = XCNEWVAR (char, cl_options_count);
1137
1138 if (!opts->x_help_enum_printed)
1139 opts->x_help_enum_printed = XCNEWVAR (char, cl_enums_count);
1140
1141 for (i = 0; i < cl_options_count; i++)
1142 {
1143 const struct cl_option *option = cl_options + i;
1144 unsigned int len;
1145 const char *opt;
1146 const char *tab;
1147
1148 if (include_flags == 0
1149 || ((option->flags & include_flags) != include_flags))
1150 {
1151 if ((option->flags & any_flags) == 0)
1152 continue;
1153 }
1154
1155 /* Skip unwanted switches. */
1156 if ((option->flags & exclude_flags) != 0)
1157 continue;
1158
1159 /* The driver currently prints its own help text. */
1160 if ((option->flags & CL_DRIVER) != 0
1161 && (option->flags & (((1U << cl_lang_count) - 1)
1162 | CL_COMMON | CL_TARGET)) == 0)
1163 continue;
1164
1165 found = true;
1166 /* Skip switches that have already been printed. */
1167 if (opts->x_help_printed[i])
1168 continue;
1169
1170 opts->x_help_printed[i] = true;
1171
1172 help = option->help;
1173 if (help == NULL)
1174 {
1175 if (exclude_flags & CL_UNDOCUMENTED)
1176 continue;
1177
1178 help = undocumented_msg;
1179 }
1180
1181 if (option->alias_target < N_OPTS
1182 && cl_options [option->alias_target].help)
1183 {
1184 if (help == undocumented_msg)
1185 {
1186 /* For undocumented options that are aliases for other options
1187 that are documented, point the reader to the other option in
1188 preference of the former. */
1189 snprintf (new_help, sizeof new_help,
1190 _("Same as %s. Use the latter option instead."),
1191 cl_options [option->alias_target].opt_text);
1192 }
1193 else
1194 {
1195 /* For documented options with aliases, mention the aliased
1196 option's name for reference. */
1197 snprintf (new_help, sizeof new_help,
1198 _("%s Same as %s."),
1199 help, cl_options [option->alias_target].opt_text);
1200 }
1201
1202 help = new_help;
1203 }
1204
1205 if (option->warn_message)
1206 {
1207 /* Mention that the use of the option will trigger a warning. */
1208 if (help == new_help)
1209 snprintf (new_help + strlen (new_help),
1210 sizeof new_help - strlen (new_help),
1211 " %s", _(use_diagnosed_msg));
1212 else
1213 snprintf (new_help, sizeof new_help,
1214 "%s %s", help, _(use_diagnosed_msg));
1215
1216 help = new_help;
1217 }
1218
1219 /* Get the translation. */
1220 help = _(help);
1221
1222 /* Find the gap between the name of the
1223 option and its descriptive text. */
1224 tab = strchr (help, '\t');
1225 if (tab)
1226 {
1227 len = tab - help;
1228 opt = help;
1229 help = tab + 1;
1230 }
1231 else
1232 {
1233 opt = option->opt_text;
1234 len = strlen (opt);
1235 }
1236
1237 /* With the -Q option enabled we change the descriptive text associated
1238 with an option to be an indication of its current setting. */
1239 if (!opts->x_quiet_flag)
1240 {
1241 void *flag_var = option_flag_var (i, opts);
1242
1243 if (len < (LEFT_COLUMN + 2))
1244 strcpy (new_help, "\t\t");
1245 else
1246 strcpy (new_help, "\t");
1247
1248 if (flag_var != NULL
1249 && option->var_type != CLVC_DEFER)
1250 {
1251 if (option->flags & CL_JOINED)
1252 {
1253 if (option->var_type == CLVC_STRING)
1254 {
1255 if (* (const char **) flag_var != NULL)
1256 snprintf (new_help + strlen (new_help),
1257 sizeof (new_help) - strlen (new_help),
1258 "%s", * (const char **) flag_var);
1259 }
1260 else if (option->var_type == CLVC_ENUM)
1261 {
1262 const struct cl_enum *e = &cl_enums[option->var_enum];
1263 int value;
1264 const char *arg = NULL;
1265
1266 value = e->get (flag_var);
1267 enum_value_to_arg (e->values, &arg, value, lang_mask);
1268 if (arg == NULL)
1269 arg = _("[default]");
1270 snprintf (new_help + strlen (new_help),
1271 sizeof (new_help) - strlen (new_help),
1272 "%s", arg);
1273 }
1274 else
1275 sprintf (new_help + strlen (new_help),
1276 "%d", * (int *) flag_var);
1277 }
1278 else
1279 strcat (new_help, option_enabled (i, opts)
1280 ? _("[enabled]") : _("[disabled]"));
1281 }
1282
1283 help = new_help;
1284 }
1285
1286 wrap_help (help, opt, len, columns);
1287 displayed = true;
1288
1289 if (option->var_type == CLVC_ENUM
1290 && opts->x_help_enum_printed[option->var_enum] != 2)
1291 opts->x_help_enum_printed[option->var_enum] = 1;
1292 }
1293
1294 if (! found)
1295 {
1296 unsigned int langs = include_flags & CL_LANG_ALL;
1297
1298 if (langs == 0)
1299 printf (_(" No options with the desired characteristics were found\n"));
1300 else
1301 {
1302 unsigned int i;
1303
1304 /* PR 31349: Tell the user how to see all of the
1305 options supported by a specific front end. */
1306 for (i = 0; (1U << i) < CL_LANG_ALL; i ++)
1307 if ((1U << i) & langs)
1308 printf (_(" None found. Use --help=%s to show *all* the options supported by the %s front-end.\n"),
1309 lang_names[i], lang_names[i]);
1310 }
1311
1312 }
1313 else if (! displayed)
1314 printf (_(" All options with the desired characteristics have already been displayed\n"));
1315
1316 putchar ('\n');
1317
1318 /* Print details of enumerated option arguments, if those
1319 enumerations have help text headings provided. If no help text
1320 is provided, presume that the possible values are listed in the
1321 help text for the relevant options. */
1322 for (i = 0; i < cl_enums_count; i++)
1323 {
1324 unsigned int j, pos;
1325
1326 if (opts->x_help_enum_printed[i] != 1)
1327 continue;
1328 if (cl_enums[i].help == NULL)
1329 continue;
1330 printf (" %s\n ", _(cl_enums[i].help));
1331 pos = 4;
1332 for (j = 0; cl_enums[i].values[j].arg != NULL; j++)
1333 {
1334 unsigned int len = strlen (cl_enums[i].values[j].arg);
1335
1336 if (pos > 4 && pos + 1 + len <= columns)
1337 {
1338 printf (" %s", cl_enums[i].values[j].arg);
1339 pos += 1 + len;
1340 }
1341 else
1342 {
1343 if (pos > 4)
1344 {
1345 printf ("\n ");
1346 pos = 4;
1347 }
1348 printf ("%s", cl_enums[i].values[j].arg);
1349 pos += len;
1350 }
1351 }
1352 printf ("\n\n");
1353 opts->x_help_enum_printed[i] = 2;
1354 }
1355}
1356
1357/* Display help for a specified type of option.
1358 The options must have ALL of the INCLUDE_FLAGS set
1359 ANY of the flags in the ANY_FLAGS set
1360 and NONE of the EXCLUDE_FLAGS set. The current option state is in
1361 OPTS; LANG_MASK is used for interpreting enumerated option state. */
1362static void
1363print_specific_help (unsigned int include_flags,
1364 unsigned int exclude_flags,
1365 unsigned int any_flags,
1366 struct gcc_options *opts,
1367 unsigned int lang_mask)
1368{
1369 unsigned int all_langs_mask = (1U << cl_lang_count) - 1;
1370 const char * description = NULL;
1371 const char * descrip_extra = "";
1372 size_t i;
1373 unsigned int flag;
1374
1375 /* Sanity check: Make sure that we do not have more
1376 languages than we have bits available to enumerate them. */
1377 gcc_assert ((1U << cl_lang_count) <= CL_MIN_OPTION_CLASS);
1378
1379 /* If we have not done so already, obtain
1380 the desired maximum width of the output. */
1381 if (opts->x_help_columns == 0)
1382 {
1383 opts->x_help_columns = get_terminal_width ();
1384 if (opts->x_help_columns == INT_MAX)
1385 /* Use a reasonable default. */
1386 opts->x_help_columns = 80;
1387 }
1388
1389 /* Decide upon the title for the options that we are going to display. */
1390 for (i = 0, flag = 1; flag <= CL_MAX_OPTION_CLASS; flag <<= 1, i ++)
1391 {
1392 switch (flag & include_flags)
1393 {
1394 case 0:
1395 case CL_DRIVER:
1396 break;
1397
1398 case CL_TARGET:
1399 description = _("The following options are target specific");
1400 break;
1401 case CL_WARNING:
1402 description = _("The following options control compiler warning messages");
1403 break;
1404 case CL_OPTIMIZATION:
1405 description = _("The following options control optimizations");
1406 break;
1407 case CL_COMMON:
1408 description = _("The following options are language-independent");
1409 break;
1410 case CL_PARAMS:
1411 description = _("The --param option recognizes the following as parameters");
1412 break;
1413 default:
1414 if (i >= cl_lang_count)
1415 break;
1416 if (exclude_flags & all_langs_mask)
1417 description = _("The following options are specific to just the language ");
1418 else
1419 description = _("The following options are supported by the language ");
1420 descrip_extra = lang_names [i];
1421 break;
1422 }
1423 }
1424
1425 if (description == NULL)
1426 {
1427 if (any_flags == 0)
1428 {
1429 if (include_flags & CL_UNDOCUMENTED)
1430 description = _("The following options are not documented");
1431 else if (include_flags & CL_SEPARATE)
1432 description = _("The following options take separate arguments");
1433 else if (include_flags & CL_JOINED)
1434 description = _("The following options take joined arguments");
1435 else
1436 {
1437 internal_error ("unrecognized include_flags 0x%x passed to print_specific_help",
1438 include_flags);
1439 return;
1440 }
1441 }
1442 else
1443 {
1444 if (any_flags & all_langs_mask)
1445 description = _("The following options are language-related");
1446 else
1447 description = _("The following options are language-independent");
1448 }
1449 }
1450
1451 printf ("%s%s:\n", description, descrip_extra);
1452 print_filtered_help (include_flags, exclude_flags, any_flags,
1453 opts->x_help_columns, opts, lang_mask);
1454}

1542/* A struct for describing a run of chars within a string. */
1543
1544struct string_fragment
1545{
1546 string_fragment (const char *start, size_t len)
1547 : m_start (start), m_len (len) {}
1548
1549 const char *m_start;
1550 size_t m_len;
1551};
1552
1553/* Specialization of edit_distance_traits for string_fragment,
1554 for use by get_closest_sanitizer_option. */
1555
1556template <>
1557struct edit_distance_traits<const string_fragment &>
1558{
1559 static size_t get_length (const string_fragment &fragment)
1560 {
1561 return fragment.m_len;
1562 }
1563
1564 static const char *get_string (const string_fragment &fragment)
1565 {
1566 return fragment.m_start;
1567 }
1568};

1570/* Given ARG, an unrecognized sanitizer option, return the best
1571 matching sanitizer option, or NULL if there isn't one.
1572 CODE is OPT_fsanitize_ or OPT_fsanitize_recover_.
1573 VALUE is non-zero for the regular form of the option, zero
1574 for the "no-" form (e.g. "-fno-sanitize-recover="). */
1575
1576static const char *
1577get_closest_sanitizer_option (const string_fragment &arg,
1578 enum opt_code code, int value)
1579{
1580 best_match <const string_fragment &, const char*> bm (arg);
1581 for (int i = 0; sanitizer_opts[i].name != NULL; ++i)
1582 {
1583 /* -fsanitize=all is not valid, so don't offer it. */
1584 if (sanitizer_opts[i].flag == ~0U
1585 && code == OPT_fsanitize_
1586 && value)
1587 continue;
1588
1589 /* For -fsanitize-recover= (and not -fno-sanitize-recover=),
1590 don't offer the non-recoverable options. */
1591 if (!sanitizer_opts[i].can_recover
1592 && code == OPT_fsanitize_recover_
1593 && value)
1594 continue;
1595
1596 bm.consider (sanitizer_opts[i].name);
1597 }
1598 return bm.get_best_meaningful_candidate ();
1599}
1600
1601/* Parse comma separated sanitizer suboptions from P for option SCODE,
1602 adjust previous FLAGS and return new ones. If COMPLAIN is false,
1603 don't issue diagnostics. */
1604
1605unsigned int
1606parse_sanitizer_options (const char *p, location_t loc, int scode,
1607 unsigned int flags, int value, bool complain)
1608{
1609 enum opt_code code = (enum opt_code) scode;
1610 while (*p != 0)
1611 {
1612 size_t len, i;
1613 bool found = false;
1614 const char *comma = strchr (p, ',');
1615
1616 if (comma == NULL)
1617 len = strlen (p);
1618 else
1619 len = comma - p;
1620 if (len == 0)
1621 {
1622 p = comma + 1;
1623 continue;
1624 }
1625
1626 /* Check to see if the string matches an option class name. */
1627 for (i = 0; sanitizer_opts[i].name != NULL; ++i)
1628 if (len == sanitizer_opts[i].len
1629 && memcmp (p, sanitizer_opts[i].name, len) == 0)
1630 {
1631 /* Handle both -fsanitize and -fno-sanitize cases. */
1632 if (value && sanitizer_opts[i].flag == ~0U)
1633 {
1634 if (code == OPT_fsanitize_)
1635 {
1636 if (complain)
1637 error_at (loc, "-fsanitize=all option is not valid");
1638 }
1639 else
1640 flags |= ~(SANITIZE_THREAD | SANITIZE_LEAK
1641 | SANITIZE_UNREACHABLE | SANITIZE_RETURN);
1642 }
1643 else if (value)
1644 {
1645 /* Do not enable -fsanitize-recover=unreachable and
1646 -fsanitize-recover=return if -fsanitize-recover=undefined
1647 is selected. */
1648 if (code == OPT_fsanitize_recover_
1649 && sanitizer_opts[i].flag == SANITIZE_UNDEFINED)
1650 flags |= (SANITIZE_UNDEFINED
1651 & ~(SANITIZE_UNREACHABLE | SANITIZE_RETURN));
1652 else
1653 flags |= sanitizer_opts[i].flag;
1654 }
1655 else
1656 flags &= ~sanitizer_opts[i].flag;
1657 found = true;
1658 break;
1659 }
1660
1661 if (! found && complain)
1662 {
1663 const char *hint
1664 = get_closest_sanitizer_option (string_fragment (p, len),
1665 code, value);
1666
1667 if (hint)
1668 error_at (loc,
1669 "unrecognized argument to -f%ssanitize%s= option: %q.*s;"
1670 " did you mean %qs?",
1671 value ? "" : "no-",
1672 code == OPT_fsanitize_ ? "" : "-recover",
1673 (int) len, p, hint);
1674 else
1675 error_at (loc,
1676 "unrecognized argument to -f%ssanitize%s= option: %q.*s",
1677 value ? "" : "no-",
1678 code == OPT_fsanitize_ ? "" : "-recover",
1679 (int) len, p);
1680 }
1681
1682 if (comma == NULL)
1683 break;
1684 p = comma + 1;
1685 }
1686 return flags;
1687}
1688
1689/* Handle target- and language-independent options. Return zero to
1690 generate an "unknown option" message. Only options that need
1691 extra handling need to be listed here; if you simply want
1692 DECODED->value assigned to a variable, it happens automatically. */
1693
1694bool
1695common_handle_option (struct gcc_options *opts,
1696 struct gcc_options *opts_set,
1697 const struct cl_decoded_option *decoded,
1698 unsigned int lang_mask, int kind ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
1699 location_t loc,
1700 const struct cl_option_handlers *handlers,
1701 diagnostic_context *dc,
1702 void (*target_option_override_hook) (void))
1703{
1704 size_t scode = decoded->opt_index;
1705 const char *arg = decoded->arg;
1706 int value = decoded->value;
1707 enum opt_code code = (enum opt_code) scode;
1708
1709 gcc_assert (decoded->canonical_option_num_elements <= 2);
1710
1711 switch (code)
1712 {
1713 case OPT__param:
1714 handle_param (opts, opts_set, loc, arg);
1715 break;
1716
1717 case OPT__help:
1718 {
1719 unsigned int all_langs_mask = (1U << cl_lang_count) - 1;
1720 unsigned int undoc_mask;
1721 unsigned int i;
1722
1723 if (lang_mask == CL_DRIVER)
1724 break;
1725
1726 undoc_mask = ((opts->x_verbose_flag | opts->x_extra_warnings)
1727 ? 0
1728 : CL_UNDOCUMENTED);
1729 target_option_override_hook ();
1730 /* First display any single language specific options. */
1731 for (i = 0; i < cl_lang_count; i++)
1732 print_specific_help
1733 (1U << i, (all_langs_mask & (~ (1U << i))) | undoc_mask, 0, opts,
1734 lang_mask);
1735 /* Next display any multi language specific options. */
1736 print_specific_help (0, undoc_mask, all_langs_mask, opts, lang_mask);
1737 /* Then display any remaining, non-language options. */
1738 for (i = CL_MIN_OPTION_CLASS; i <= CL_MAX_OPTION_CLASS; i <<= 1)
1739 if (i != CL_DRIVER)
1740 print_specific_help (i, undoc_mask, 0, opts, lang_mask);
1741 opts->x_exit_after_options = true;
1742 break;
1743 }
1744
1745 case OPT__target_help:
1746 if (lang_mask == CL_DRIVER)
1747 break;
1748
1749 target_option_override_hook ();
1750 print_specific_help (CL_TARGET, CL_UNDOCUMENTED, 0, opts, lang_mask);
1751 opts->x_exit_after_options = true;
1752 break;
1753
1754 case OPT__help_:
1755 {
1756 const char *a = arg;
1757 unsigned int include_flags = 0;
1758 /* Note - by default we include undocumented options when listing
1759 specific classes. If you only want to see documented options
1760 then add ",^undocumented" to the --help= option. E.g.:
1761
1762 --help=target,^undocumented */
1763 unsigned int exclude_flags = 0;
1764
1765 if (lang_mask == CL_DRIVER)
1766 break;
1767
1768 /* Walk along the argument string, parsing each word in turn.
1769 The format is:
1770 arg = [^]{word}[,{arg}]
1771 word = {optimizers|target|warnings|undocumented|
1772 params|common|<language>} */
1773 while (*a != 0)
1774 {
1775 static const struct
1776 {
1777 const char *string;
1778 unsigned int flag;
1779 }
1780 specifics[] =
1781 {
1782 { "optimizers", CL_OPTIMIZATION },
1783 { "target", CL_TARGET },
1784 { "warnings", CL_WARNING },
1785 { "undocumented", CL_UNDOCUMENTED },
1786 { "params", CL_PARAMS },
1787 { "joined", CL_JOINED },
1788 { "separate", CL_SEPARATE },
1789 { "common", CL_COMMON },
1790 { NULL, 0 }
1791 };
1792 unsigned int *pflags;
1793 const char *comma;
1794 unsigned int lang_flag, specific_flag;
1795 unsigned int len;
1796 unsigned int i;
1797
1798 if (*a == '^')
1799 {
1800 ++a;
1801 if (*a == '\0')
1802 {
1803 error_at (loc, "missing argument to %qs", "--help=^");
1804 break;
1805 }
1806 pflags = &exclude_flags;
1807 }
1808 else
1809 pflags = &include_flags;
1810
1811 comma = strchr (a, ',');
1812 if (comma == NULL)
1813 len = strlen (a);
1814 else
1815 len = comma - a;
1816 if (len == 0)
1817 {
1818 a = comma + 1;
1819 continue;
1820 }
1821
1822 /* Check to see if the string matches an option class name. */
1823 for (i = 0, specific_flag = 0; specifics[i].string != NULL; i++)
1824 if (strncasecmp (a, specifics[i].string, len) == 0)
1825 {
1826 specific_flag = specifics[i].flag;
1827 break;
1828 }
1829
1830 /* Check to see if the string matches a language name.
1831 Note - we rely upon the alpha-sorted nature of the entries in
1832 the lang_names array, specifically that shorter names appear
1833 before their longer variants. (i.e. C before C++). That way
1834 when we are attempting to match --help=c for example we will
1835 match with C first and not C++. */
1836 for (i = 0, lang_flag = 0; i < cl_lang_count; i++)
1837 if (strncasecmp (a, lang_names[i], len) == 0)
1838 {
1839 lang_flag = 1U << i;
1840 break;
1841 }
1842
1843 if (specific_flag != 0)
1844 {
1845 if (lang_flag == 0)
1846 *pflags |= specific_flag;
1847 else
1848 {
1849 /* The option's argument matches both the start of a
1850 language name and the start of an option class name.
1851 We have a special case for when the user has
1852 specified "--help=c", but otherwise we have to issue
1853 a warning. */
1854 if (strncasecmp (a, "c", len) == 0)
1855 *pflags |= lang_flag;
1856 else
1857 warning_at (loc, 0,
1858 "--help argument %q.*s is ambiguous, "
1859 "please be more specific",
1860 len, a);
1861 }
1862 }
1863 else if (lang_flag != 0)
1864 *pflags |= lang_flag;
1865 else
1866 warning_at (loc, 0,
1867 "unrecognized argument to --help= option: %q.*s",
1868 len, a);
1869
1870 if (comma == NULL)
1871 break;
1872 a = comma + 1;
1873 }
1874
1875 if (include_flags)
1876 {
1877 target_option_override_hook ();
1878 print_specific_help (include_flags, exclude_flags, 0, opts,
1879 lang_mask);
1880 }
1881 opts->x_exit_after_options = true;
1882 break;
1883 }
1884
1885 case OPT__version:
1886 if (lang_mask == CL_DRIVER)
1887 break;
1888
1889 opts->x_exit_after_options = true;
1890 break;
1891
1892 case OPT_fsanitize_:
1893 opts->x_flag_sanitize
1894 = parse_sanitizer_options (arg, loc, code,
1895 opts->x_flag_sanitize, value, true);
1896
1897 /* Kernel ASan implies normal ASan but does not yet support

2386/* Handle --param NAME=VALUE. */
2387static void
2388handle_param (struct gcc_options *opts, struct gcc_options *opts_set,
2389 location_t loc, const char *carg)
2390{
2391 char *equal, *arg;
2392 int value;
2393
2394 arg = xstrdup (carg);
2395 equal = strchr (arg, '=');
2396 if (!equal)
2397 error_at (loc, "%s: --param arguments should be of the form NAME=VALUE",
2398 arg);
2399 else
2400 {
2401 *equal = '\0';
2402
2403 enum compiler_param index;
2404 if (!find_param (arg, &index))
2405 {
2406 const char *suggestion = find_param_fuzzy (arg);
2407 if (suggestion)
2408 error_at (loc, "invalid --param name %qs; did you mean %qs?",
2409 arg, suggestion);
2410 else
2411 error_at (loc, "invalid --param name %qs", arg);
2412 }
2413 else
2414 {
2415 if (!param_string_value_p (index, equal + 1, &value))
2416 value = integral_argument (equal + 1);
2417
2418 if (value == -1)
2419 error_at (loc, "invalid --param value %qs", equal + 1);
2420 else
2421 set_param_value (arg, value,
2422 opts->x_param_values, opts_set->x_param_values);
2423 }
2424 }
2425
2426 free (arg);
2427}

2430 when no level is specified (i.e., when -Wstrict-aliasing, and not
2431 -Wstrict-aliasing=level was given).
2432 ONOFF is assumed to take value 1 when -Wstrict-aliasing is specified,
2433 and 0 otherwise. After calling this function, wstrict_aliasing will be
2434 set to the default value of -Wstrict_aliasing=level, currently 3. */
2435static void
2436set_Wstrict_aliasing (struct gcc_options *opts, int onoff)

2438 gcc_assert (onoff == 0 || onoff == 1);
2439 if (onoff != 0)

2441 else
2442 opts->x_warn_strict_aliasing = 0;
2443}

2468 opts->x_flag_rounding_math = 0;
2469 if (!opts->frontend_set_flag_cx_limited_range)
2470 opts->x_flag_cx_limited_range = 1;
2471 }

2514/* Handle a debug output -g switch for options OPTS
2515 (OPTS_SET->x_write_symbols storing whether a debug type was passed
2516 explicitly), location LOC. EXTENDED is true or false to support
2517 extended output (2 is special and means "-ggdb" was given). */
2518static void
2519set_debug_level (enum debug_info_type type, int extended, const char *arg,
2520 struct gcc_options *opts, struct gcc_options *opts_set,
2521 location_t loc)
2522{
2523 opts->x_use_gnu_debug_info_extensions = extended;
2524
2525 if (type == NO_DEBUG)
2526 {
2527 if (opts->x_write_symbols == NO_DEBUG)
2528 {
2529 opts->x_write_symbols = PREFERRED_DEBUGGING_TYPE;
2530
2531 if (extended == 2)
2532 {
2533#if defined DWARF2_DEBUGGING_INFO || defined DWARF2_LINENO_DEBUGGING_INFO
2534 opts->x_write_symbols = DWARF2_DEBUG;
2535#elif defined DBX_DEBUGGING_INFO
2536 opts->x_write_symbols = DBX_DEBUG;
2537#endif
2538 }
2539
2540 if (opts->x_write_symbols == NO_DEBUG)
2541 warning_at (loc, 0, "target system does not support debug output");
2542 }
2543 }
2544 else
2545 {
2546 /* Does it conflict with an already selected type? */
2547 if (opts_set->x_write_symbols != NO_DEBUG
2548 && opts->x_write_symbols != NO_DEBUG
2549 && type != opts->x_write_symbols)
2550 error_at (loc, "debug format %qs conflicts with prior selection",
2551 debug_type_names[type]);
2552 opts->x_write_symbols = type;
2553 opts_set->x_write_symbols = type;
2554 }
2555
2556 /* A debug flag without a level defaults to level 2.
2557 If off or at level 1, set it to level 2, but if already
2558 at level 3, don't lower it. */
2559 if (*arg == '\0')
2560 {
2561 if (opts->x_debug_info_level < DINFO_LEVEL_NORMAL)
2562 opts->x_debug_info_level = DINFO_LEVEL_NORMAL;
2563 }
2564 else
2565 {
2566 int argval = integral_argument (arg);
2567 if (argval == -1)
2568 error_at (loc, "unrecognized debug output level %qs", arg);
2569 else if (argval > 3)
2570 error_at (loc, "debug output level %qs is too high", arg);
2571 else
2572 opts->x_debug_info_level = (enum debug_info_levels) argval;
2573 }
2574}

2576/* Arrange to dump core on error for diagnostic context DC. (The
2577 regular error message is still printed first, except in the case of
2578 abort ().) */
2579
2580static void
2581setup_core_dumping (diagnostic_context *dc)
2582{
2583#ifdef SIGABRT
2584 signal (SIGABRT, SIG_DFL);
2585#endif
2586#if defined(HAVE_SETRLIMIT)
2587 {
2588 struct rlimit rlim;
2589 if (getrlimit (RLIMIT_CORE, &rlim) != 0)
2590 fatal_error (input_location, "getting core file size maximum limit: %m");
2591 rlim.rlim_cur = rlim.rlim_max;
2592 if (setrlimit (RLIMIT_CORE, &rlim) != 0)
2593 fatal_error (input_location,
2594 "setting core file size limit to maximum: %m");
2595 }
2596#endif
2597 diagnostic_abort_on_error (dc);
2598}

2600/* Parse a -d<ARG> command line switch for OPTS, location LOC,
2601 diagnostic context DC. */
2602
2603static void
2604decode_d_option (const char *arg, struct gcc_options *opts,
2605 location_t loc, diagnostic_context *dc)
2606{
2607 int c;
2608
2609 while (*arg)
2610 switch (c = *arg++)
2611 {
2612 case 'A':
2613 opts->x_flag_debug_asm = 1;
2614 break;
2615 case 'p':
2616 opts->x_flag_print_asm_name = 1;
2617 break;
2618 case 'P':
2619 opts->x_flag_dump_rtl_in_asm = 1;
2620 opts->x_flag_print_asm_name = 1;
2621 break;
2622 case 'x':
2623 opts->x_rtl_dump_and_exit = 1;
2624 break;
2625 case 'D': /* These are handled by the preprocessor. */
2626 case 'I':
2627 case 'M':
2628 case 'N':
2629 case 'U':
2630 break;
2631 case 'H':
2632 setup_core_dumping (dc);
2633 break;
2634 case 'a':
2635 opts->x_flag_dump_all_passed = true;
2636 break;
2637
2638 default:
2639 warning_at (loc, 0, "unrecognized gcc debugging option: %c", c);
2640 break;
2641 }
2642}

2644/* Enable (or disable if VALUE is 0) a warning option ARG (language
2645 mask LANG_MASK, option handlers HANDLERS) as an error for option
2646 structures OPTS and OPTS_SET, diagnostic context DC (possibly
2647 NULL), location LOC. This is used by -Werror=. */
2648
2649static void
2650enable_warning_as_error (const char *arg, int value, unsigned int lang_mask,
2651 const struct cl_option_handlers *handlers,
2652 struct gcc_options *opts,
2653 struct gcc_options *opts_set,
2654 location_t loc, diagnostic_context *dc)
2655{
2656 char *new_option;
2657 int option_index;
2658
2659 new_option = XNEWVEC (char, strlen (arg) + 2);
2660 new_option[0] = 'W';
2661 strcpy (new_option + 1, arg);
2662 option_index = find_opt (new_option, lang_mask);
2663 if (option_index == OPT_SPECIAL_unknown)
2664 error_at (loc, "-Werror=%s: no option -%s", arg, new_option);
2665 else if (!(cl_options[option_index].flags & CL_WARNING))
2666 error_at (loc, "-Werror=%s: -%s is not an option that controls warnings",
2667 arg, new_option);
2668 else
2669 {
2670 const diagnostic_t kind = value ? DK_ERROR : DK_WARNING;
2671 const char *arg = NULL;
2672
2673 if (cl_options[option_index].flags & CL_JOINED)
2674 arg = new_option + cl_options[option_index].opt_len;
2675 control_warning_option (option_index, (int) kind, arg, value,
2676 loc, lang_mask,
2677 handlers, opts, opts_set, dc);
2678 }
2679 free (new_option);
2680}

2682/* Return malloced memory for the name of the option OPTION_INDEX
2683 which enabled a diagnostic (context CONTEXT), originally of type
2684 ORIG_DIAG_KIND but possibly converted to DIAG_KIND by options such
2685 as -Werror. */
2686
2687char *
2688option_name (diagnostic_context *context, int option_index,
2689 diagnostic_t orig_diag_kind, diagnostic_t diag_kind)
2690{
2691 if (option_index)
2692 {
2693 /* A warning classified as an error. */
2694 if ((orig_diag_kind == DK_WARNING || orig_diag_kind == DK_PEDWARN)
2695 && diag_kind == DK_ERROR)
2696 return concat (cl_options[OPT_Werror_].opt_text,
2697 /* Skip over "-W". */
2698 cl_options[option_index].opt_text + 2,
2699 NULL);
2700 /* A warning with option. */
2701 else
2702 return xstrdup (cl_options[option_index].opt_text);
2703 }
2704 /* A warning without option classified as an error. */
2705 else if ((orig_diag_kind == DK_WARNING || orig_diag_kind == DK_PEDWARN
2706 || diag_kind == DK_WARNING)
2707 && context->warning_as_error_requested)
2708 return xstrdup (cl_options[OPT_Werror].opt_text);
2709 else
2710 return NULL;
2711}
